---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Medicaid Waiver Info"
  description="Learn what the Medicaid Waiver is, how it works in Indiana, and how Alved Services can help you or your loved one access services at no cost."
>

  <!-- PAGE HERO -->
  <section class="page-hero" aria-label="Medicaid Waiver Information">
    <div class="wrap page-hero-inner reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Medicaid Waiver</span>
      <h1>What is the Medicaid Waiver, and how can it help you?</h1>
      <p class="lead">The Medicaid Waiver helps adults with intellectual and developmental disabilities get the support they need at home and in their community, at no cost to you if you qualify. We are here to help you understand it.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-gold">Press here to Talk to Us About Getting Started</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PLAIN LANGUAGE EXPLAINER -->
  <section class="explainer-section" aria-labelledby="explainer-heading">
    <div class="explainer-bg-shape" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="wrap explainer-inner">
      <div class="explainer-text reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">In Plain Language</span>
        <h2 id="explainer-heading">What it means for you</h2>
        <p>Medicaid Waivers, sometimes called Home and Community Based Services (HCBS), allow Medicaid to fund supports and services for children and adults with disabilities in their family homes or community residential programs instead of institutions. Medicaid Waivers allow an individual to use traditional Medicaid services and the additional services available through the Medicaid Waiver program.</p>
        <p>The Medicaid Waiver changes that. Individuals can now be supported to live in their own home and engage in the community, as they choose.</p>
        <p>For more information regarding the Medicaid Waiver program, contact the Bureau of Developmental Services (BDS). If you or your loved one qualifies, services are covered by Medicaid, at no cost to you.</p>
        <a href="https://www.in.gov/fssa/ddrs/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="btn btn-primary">Press here to Visit the Official BDS Website ↗</a>
      </div>
      <div class="explainer-card reveal reveal--delay">
        <div class="explainer-card-top" aria-hidden="true">
          <div class="ec-sun"></div>
          <div class="ec-shield"></div>
        </div>
        <h3>The simple version</h3>
        <ul class="simple-list" role="list">
          <li>
            <span class="simple-num" aria-label="Step 1">1</span>
            <div><strong>You qualify</strong><p>Based on your diagnosis and level of need, assessed by the state.</p></div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="simple-num" aria-label="Step 2">2</span>
            <div><strong>You choose a provider</strong><p>Such as Alved Services, a BDS-approved provider agency to deliver your services.</p></div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="simple-num" aria-label="Step 3">3</span>
            <div><strong>Services are planned with you</strong><p>A support team builds a plan around your goals and desires. Your voice, your choice.</p></div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="simple-num" aria-label="Step 4">4</span>
            <div><strong>Medicaid covers the cost</strong><p>No out-of-pocket cost to eligible individuals. The waiver program supports your home and community based services (HCBS) needs.</p></div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- BENEFITS -->
  <section class="benefits-section" aria-labelledby="benefits-heading">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">How It Helps</span>
        <h2 id="benefits-heading">What the Medicaid Waiver provides for you</h2>
        <p>Services are planned with you, your family, and your support team, always focused on what matters most to you.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="benefits-grid" role="list">
        <article class="benefit-card reveal" role="listitem">
          <div class="benefit-icon" aria-hidden="true">🏠</div>
          <h3>Support at Home & in Your Community</h3>
          <p>You can live where you feel most comfortable and stay connected to your family, friends, and the activities you enjoy.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="benefit-card reveal reveal--delay" role="listitem">
          <div class="benefit-icon" aria-hidden="true">✋</div>
          <h3>Your Personal Choice</h3>
          <p>You have a say in your services, your goals, and your daily routine. Support is built around you, not the system.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="benefit-card reveal reveal--delay-2" role="listitem">
          <div class="benefit-icon" aria-hidden="true">📈</div>
          <h3>Building Your Skills & Independence</h3>
          <p>Supports focus on helping you learn new skills and do more on your own over time.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="benefit-card reveal" role="listitem">
          <div class="benefit-icon" aria-hidden="true">👨‍👩‍👧</div>
          <h3>Support for Your Family</h3>
          <p>Your family can feel confident knowing you are receiving caring and reliable support.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="benefit-card reveal reveal--delay" role="listitem">
          <div class="benefit-icon" aria-hidden="true">💚</div>
          <h3>No Cost to Eligible Individuals</h3>
          <p>Services are covered by Medicaid for those who qualify. There is no out-of-pocket cost to you.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="benefit-card reveal reveal--delay-2" role="listitem">
          <div class="benefit-icon" aria-hidden="true">🤝</div>
          <h3>Coordinated Support</h3>
          <p>A program manager helps navigate services, connect you with providers, and make sure your plan stays on track.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- APPROVED PROGRAMS -->
  <section class="programs-section" aria-labelledby="programs-heading">
    <div class="programs-bg-shape" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">Alved Services Approved Programs</span>
        <h2 id="programs-heading">The programs we are approved to provide</h2>
        <p>Alved Services is a CQL-accredited, BDS-approved provider for the following Medicaid Waiver programs in Indiana.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="programs-grid">
        <article class="program-card reveal">
          <div class="program-card-accent"></div>
          <h3>Community Integration Waiver</h3>
          <p>Supports adults with intellectual and developmental disabilities to live independently and participate fully in community life, at home and in the community rather than in a facility.</p>
          <ul class="program-services" role="list">
            <li>Residential Habilitation & Support (RHS)</li>
            <li>Community Integration Habilitation (CIH)</li>
            <li>Participant Assistance & Care (PAC)</li>
            <li>Adult Day Services</li>
            <li>Respite</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
        <article class="program-card reveal reveal--delay">
          <div class="program-card-accent program-card-accent--gold"></div>
          <h3>Family Support Waiver</h3>
          <p>Helps adults with intellectual and developmental disabilities who live with their families to get the support they need while staying connected to home and family life.</p>
          <ul class="program-services" role="list">
            <li>Participant Assistance & Care (PAC)</li>
            <li>Adult Day Services</li>
            <li>Respite</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
        <article class="program-card reveal reveal--delay-2">
          <div class="program-card-accent"></div>
          <h3>Money Follows the Person</h3>
          <p>A program that helps individuals transition from an institutional or facility setting back to living in the community. Alved Services is an approved provider to support individuals making this transition.</p>
          <ul class="program-services" role="list">
            <li>Transition planning support</li>
            <li>Community-based services</li>
            <li>Adult Day Services</li>
            <li>Individualized skill-building</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- EDITORIAL PHOTO -->
  <section class="editorial-section" aria-labelledby="editorial-heading">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">What It Looks Like</span>
        <h2 id="editorial-heading">Real support, real community</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="editorial-row reveal">
        <div class="editorial-img">
          <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1576765608535-5f04d1e3f289?w=800&q=80" alt="A support professional working alongside an adult individual in the community" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="editorial-text">
          <span class="ed-tag">Your Community Life</span>
          <h3>Support that fits your life</h3>
          <p>Waiver services do not require you to change where you live or how you spend your time. Support comes to you, at home, at work, or in the community, built around your routine and your goals.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="faq-section" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
    <div class="faq-bg-shape" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">Common Questions</span>
        <h2 id="faq-heading">Questions families ask us</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-grid reveal">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Who qualifies for the Medicaid Waiver?</h3>
          <p>Adults with an intellectual or developmental disability diagnosis who meet Indiana's eligibility criteria. Eligibility is assessed by the state through a formal evaluation process.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How do we get started?</h3>
          <p>Contact your program manager if you already have one, or reach out to us directly. We can help guide you through the process and connect you with the right resources.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Is there a waitlist?</h3>
          <p>Indiana does maintain a waitlist for some waiver programs. A program manager can help determine your current status and what options may be available to you now.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can we choose our own provider?</h3>
          <p>Yes. You and your family have the right to choose your provider. Alved Services is a BDS-approved provider, which means we can deliver waiver services to eligible individuals.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>What if we do not have a program manager?</h3>
          <p>We can help connect you with a program manager. Contact us and we will help point you in the right direction to get the process started.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Does this cost anything?</h3>
          <p>For eligible individuals, services covered under the Medicaid Waiver are paid for by Medicaid at no cost to you. We can help clarify what is covered based on your specific situation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="waiver-cta" aria-label="Get in touch">
    <div class="cta-bg-shape" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="wrap waiver-cta-inner reveal">
      <h2>Have questions? We are here to help you.</h2>
      <p>No pressure, no jargon, just honest answers about your options.</p>
      <div class="btn-row">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-gold">Press here to Contact Us</a>
        <a href="/services" class="btn btn-ghost-light">Press here to See Our Services</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero { position: relative; padding: 100px 0 90px; overflow: hidden; }
  .page-hero::before { content: ''; position: absolute; inset: 0; background: url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1529156069898-49953e39b3ac?w=1600&q=80') center/cover no-repeat; z-index: 0; }
  .page-hero::after { content: ''; position: absolute; inset: 0; background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(20,42,69,0.93) 0%, rgba(31,58,95,0.82) 60%, rgba(31,58,95,0.65) 100%); z-index: 1; }
  .page-hero-inner { position: relative; z-index: 2; max-width: 740px; }
  .page-hero .eyebrow { color: var(--gold-soft); }
  .page-hero h1 { color: var(--white); font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); margin-bottom: 18px; }
  .page-hero .lead { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.82); font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; max-width: 600px; margin-bottom: 28px; }
  .btn-gold { background: var(--gold); color: var(--navy-deep); font-weight: 700; }
  .btn-gold:hover { background: #a07820; transform: translateY(-1px); }

  .explainer-section { padding: var(--section-pad) 0; position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
  .explainer-bg-shape { position: absolute; top: -100px; right: -100px; width: 500px; height: 500px; border-radius: 50%; background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(184,144,44,0.06) 0%, transparent 70%); pointer-events: none; }
  .explainer-inner { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 0.9fr; gap: 60px; align-items: start; position: relative; z-index: 1; }
  .explainer-text h2 { font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.2rem); margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .explainer-text p { color: var(--ink-soft); margin-bottom: 16px; line-height: 1.75; }
  .explainer-text p:last-of-type { margin-bottom: 24px; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--navy); color: var(--white); font-weight: 700; }
  .btn-primary:hover { background: var(--navy-deep); transform: translateY(-1px); }
  .explainer-card { background: var(--navy); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 32px; }
  .explainer-card-top { display: flex; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 22px; }
  .ec-sun { width: 28px; height: 28px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--gold); box-shadow: 0 0 0 5px rgba(184,144,44,0.25); }
  .ec-shield { width: 24px; height: 28px; border: 2.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.5); border-radius: 3px 3px 10px 10px; }
  .explainer-card h3 { color: var(--white); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .simple-list { list-style: none; display: grid; gap: 18px; }
  .simple-list li { display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: flex-start; }
  .simple-num { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; width: 28px; height: 28px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--gold); color: var(--navy-deep); font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.82rem; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px; }
  .simple-list strong { display: block; color: var(--white); font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .simple-list p { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.72); font-size: 0.88rem; margin: 0; line-height: 1.5; }

  .benefits-section { padding: var(--section-pad) 0; background: var(--bg-alt); }
  .section-head { max-width: 580px; margin-bottom: 44px; }
  .section-head h2 { font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.2rem); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .section-head p { color: var(--ink-soft); }
  .benefits-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 20px; }
  .benefit-card { background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 28px; border-bottom: 4px solid var(--gold-soft); transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease, border-color 0.2s ease; }
  .benefit-card:hover { transform: translateY(-3px); box-shadow: 0 12px 30px -10px rgba(31,58,95,0.15); border-bottom-color: var(--gold); }
  .benefit-icon { font-size: 1.8rem; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .benefit-card h3 { font-size: 1.02rem; margin-bottom: 10px; color: var(--navy); }
  .benefit-card p { color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 0.92rem; margin: 0; line-height: 1.6; }

  .programs-section { padding: var(--section-pad) 0; position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
  .programs-bg-shape { position: absolute; bottom: -100px; left: -100px; width: 450px; height: 450px; border-radius: 50%; background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(184,144,44,0.06) 0%, transparent 70%); pointer-events: none; }
  .programs-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 22px; position: relative; z-index: 1; }
  .program-card { background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 32px; position: relative; overflow: hidden; transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease; }
  .program-card:hover { transform: translateY(-3px); box-shadow: 0 12px 30px -8px rgba(31,58,95,0.12); }
  .program-card-accent { position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; height: 5px; background: var(--navy); }
  .program-card-accent--gold { background: var(--gold); }
  .program-card h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 12px; color: var(--navy); }
  .program-card p { color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.65; margin-bottom: 18px; }
  .program-services { list-style: none; display: grid; gap: 6px; }
  .program-services li { font-size: 0.86rem; color: var(--ink-soft); display: flex; gap: 8px; }
  .program-services li::before { content: "→"; color: var(--gold); font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0; }

  .editorial-section { padding: var(--section-pad) 0; background: var(--bg-alt); }
  .editorial-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 50px; align-items: center; }
  .editorial-img { border-radius: var(--radius); overflow: hidden; }
  .editorial-img img { width: 100%; height: 340px; object-fit: cover; display: block; }
  .ed-tag { display: inline-block; background: var(--gold-soft); color: var(--navy-deep); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; padding: 4px 12px; border-radius: 20px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .editorial-text h3 { font-family: var(--font-head); font-size: 1.4rem; color: var(--navy); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .editorial-text p { color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.7; }

  .faq-section { padding: var(--section-pad) 0; position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
  .faq-bg-shape { position: absolute; top: -80px; right: -80px; width: 400px; height: 400px; border-radius: 50%; background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(31,58,95,0.05) 0%, transparent 70%); pointer-events: none; }
  .faq-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 24px; position: relative; z-index: 1; }
  .faq-item { background: var(--white); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 28px; border-left: 5px solid var(--gold); }
  .faq-item h3 { font-size: 1rem; color: var(--navy); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .faq-item p { color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.65; margin: 0; }

  .waiver-cta { background: var(--navy); padding: 64px 0; position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
  .cta-bg-shape { position: absolute; top: -80px; right: -80px; width: 400px; height: 400px; border-radius: 50%; background: rgba(184,144,44,0.08); pointer-events: none; }
  .waiver-cta-inner { text-align: center; max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; position: relative; z-index: 1; }
  .waiver-cta h2 { color: var(--white); font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .waiver-cta p { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75); margin-bottom: 28px; }
  .btn-row { display: flex; gap: 14px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-ghost-light { background: transparent; color: var(--white); border: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.5); font-weight: 700; }
  .btn-ghost-light:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); color: var(--white); }

  .reveal { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(18px); transition: opacity 0.6s ease, transform 0.6s ease; }
  .reveal.in { opacity: 1; transform: none; }
  .reveal--delay  { transition-delay: 0.15s; }
  .reveal--delay-2 { transition-delay: 0.3s; }

  @media (max-width: 880px) {
    .explainer-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .benefits-grid  { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
    .programs-grid  { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .faq-grid       { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .editorial-row  { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .benefits-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>

<script>
  const reveals = document.querySelectorAll('.reveal');
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
    (entries) => entries.forEach(e => { if (e.isIntersecting) { e.target.classList.add('in'); observer.unobserve(e.target); } }),
    { threshold: 0.1 }
  );
  reveals.forEach(el => observer.observe(el));
</script>